Sidharth Malhotra is currently learning different martial arts such as Krav Maga and Judo for his next movie.
TNN | May 5, 2016, 01.19 PM ISTSidharth Malhotra seems to be in action mode.
After 'Ek Villain' and 'Brothers', the actor will continue his action streak in his next film opposite Jacqueline Fernandez.
The film, which is currently untitled, will be directed by filmmaker-duo Raj Nidimoru and Krishna DK, and go on floors this week.
And to prepare for his role, the actor is currently learning different martial arts such as Krav Maga and Judo.
The film, which was rumoured to be a sequel to 'Bang Bang' (it isn't, as confirmed by Sidharth in a separate interview), will have several action sequences, particularly, hand-to-hand combat.
And keeping in mind the action theme of the movie, Sidharth is training hard to ensure that the scenes look as authentic as possible.
Parts of the film will be shot in Malaysia and Miami, with international action directors all set to provide their expertise.
Sidharth Malhotra-Jacqueline Fernandez's next not a sequel to 'Bang Bang' Bollywood actor Sidharth Malhotra says his forthcoming action-comedy film with actress Jacqueline Fernandez is not a sequel to 'Bang Bang'.
Sidharth, naturally, is elated to be doing action again.
The actor has already lost weight for the film and is working on his flexibility for the stunts.
Sidharth, whose last release was the the hit 'Kapoor & Sons', has already finished shooting for Nitya Mehra's next, 'Baar Baar Dekho', where he is paired opposite Katrina Kaif.
